**Progress Update:**

Significant progress has been made toward improving the scalability, resiliency, and operational efficiency of the VSaaS platform to support continued growth in container builds while optimizing infrastructure utilization.

I have led several performance optimization initiatives to reduce image rescan latency and improve overall scan throughput. This includes redesigning Aqua scan polling behaviour by introducing an initial wait period followed by more efficient polling intervals, as well as fine-tuning retry strategies to reduce unnecessary requests and improve end-to-end scan completion times under peak workloads.

To strengthen platform reliability within Kubernetes, I enhanced VSaaS readiness and liveness probes to align with Kubernetes best practices, improving application health detection and deployment stability. In parallel, I initiated architectural improvements to evaluate the current Uvicorn/Gunicorn runtime configuration, identifying an opportunity to deliver an estimated 10–30% performance improvement through a more optimal server model.

I also delivered optimizations that reduce unnecessary downstream load on Aqua by eliminating authentication token generation for internal health check operations. This required enhancements to the shared `aquasec-client` library, comprehensive testing, and adoption within VSaaS, resulting in reduced authentication traffic and improved platform efficiency.

To further enhance resiliency, I led improvements to VSaaS shutdown behaviour by implementing graceful SIGTERM handling. The `/health` endpoint now correctly returns HTTP 503 during termination, allowing Kubernetes to immediately stop routing new requests while existing requests complete successfully. This enhancement enables true zero-downtime deployments, minimizes service disruption during rolling upgrades, and improves overall platform availability and operational resilience.

Collectively, these enhancements have strengthened the scalability and reliability of VSaaS, improved resource utilization, reduced infrastructure overhead, and positioned the platform to support future growth while maintaining a high-quality developer experience.
